title.57: Captain Savage and His Leatherneck Raiders (1968) #1

description.0: Balder's battle with the Rock Trolls rages on! Odin pays a visit to Midgard...
description.2: The Silver Surfer has been under the protection of the FF, free from his cosmic responsibilities. But when Galactus unleashes a cyborg to retrieve his former herald, the team is swept up in a battle they don't want to fight!
description.3: Continued from Iron Man and Sub-Mariner #1! An amnesiac Sub-Mariner is trapped under tons of ice, but Destiny decides to toy with Atlantis' King further by producing memories he hasn't yet recovered!
description.4: Just as Betty is about reveal her feelings to Bruce, The Space Parasite reveals himself! Bruce is forced to transform into the Hulk, leading to an all-out brawl at Yankee Stadium! And even if the Hulk wins this battle, Bruce may lose more than he ever imagined...
description.5: PREMIERE ISSUE! The Sentry continues to wreak havoc at Cape Canaveral and it's up to Captain Marvel to put an end to it.
description.6: George Stacy has been brainwashed by the Kingpin. Spider-Man must put a stop to the Kingpin's plan, but can he do it without hurting Gwen's dad?
description.7: Black Panther Joins the Avengers!  Black Panther breaks into the Avengers Mansion only to find the entire team decimated. And what does S.H.I.E.L.D agent Jasper Sitwell want with the Panther?
description.8: Red Skull awakens the fourth Sleeper! It's up to Cap to shut the killer robot down!
description.9: When Loki transports the Hulk to Asgard, the Warriors Three rush to meet the Jade Giant!
description.10: The Unholy Three have been released from prison, and they've had plenty of time to invent new evils! When a renewed crime spree hits the streets, Daredevil springs into action. Foggy worries about his reputation as a district attorney candidate when it comes to dating ex-con Debbie. But Foggy may not have to worry...especially if Debbie is eliminated!
description.11: A historic Marvel first - the one-shot double feature that kicked off Iron Man and Sub-Mariner's very first solo series! While Iron Man must contend with both the scheming Maggia and the evil of A.I.M., Namor must battle to save his underwater realm from the darkness of Destiny!
description.13: One moment ago... The shimmering, shadowy face of the venerated ancient one materialized before the startled eyes of Dr. Strange! Now... The Mystic Master stands transfixed as the body of his mentor melts into mortal flesh!
description.14: Sif has taken the bait and become one with the Destroyer! It's a disaster all around, as Balder remains under the spell of Karnilla, while Thor does battle against Sif...unknowingly!
description.16: The FF believes that Daredevil is still inhabited by Doctor Doom, attacking the blind super hero unawares. But little does the team realize, Ol' Hornhead's got some super-powered friends of his own!
description.17: Mary Jane has taken a job as a go-go dancer. But Peter soon discovers that the club MJ works for is actually a front for a criminal enterprise, where a man named Dr. Winkler brainwashes his victims!
description.18: Thor! Iron Man! And the powers of Goliath restored!
description.19: Baron Zemo orders Agent 13 to assassinate Captain America. Can she pull the trigger?
description.23: Spencer Smythe has created a Spider-Slayer robot for J. Jonah Jameson to use against the Wallcrawler. But when Jameson fails to capture Spider-Man, Smythe takes over control with designs on killing the hero!
description.24: After his defeat, Hercules finds himself banished to another world, but it is here he finds the strength to defeat Typhon. Meanwhile, in his absence, Typhon wreaks havoc on the world. Can Hercules find a way back to earth and save the day?
description.25: Daredevil is trapped in the steely prison...of Doctor Doom's body! Stuck in a cell at the Latverian Embassy, Matt Murdock remains helpless as Doom exacts his revenge on the FF. But what trick does Matt have up his sleeve? And will our hero be reunited with his rightful body by the end of this issue?
description.27: To thwart Dr. Strange's rescue of Victoria Bentley-Yandroth has unleashed his ultimate weapon-Voltorg! And apparently nothing can stop him...
description.28: His armor - broken! His life - in peril! Tony Stark must free himself from the Maggia, or it's the end of Iron Man!
description.29: Only one weapon can be used to conquer Asgard. That weapon's name is Hulk.
description.30: Death has come for Thor...in the beauteous form of Hela! But the battle's not over yet- Balder and Sif must face Karnilla and Loki!
description.32: The Silver Surfer has seen enough of humanity to know that it must be destroyed. The Fantastic Four do battle with the cosmic wanderer, but with Sue Richards out of commission, the task at hand seems even more daunting! Will the Surfer see the error of his ways...before it's too late?
description.33: The First Appearance of Carol Danvers, who would assume the mantle of Captain Marvel!  Captain Marvel (Mar-Vell) returns and must face down a Kree threat in The Sentry!
description.34: Daredevil attacked by the Fantastic Four's worst villain! That's right; Doctor Doom has subdued Daredevil for his own dastardly plot. Why does Doom want to switch bodies with DD? Matt Murdock stands alone in his stickiest situation yet.
description.36: The Mystic and the Machine! In a world beneath a world, Dr. Strange meets Yandroth, a science lord of a vast planet! And this Lord plans to make the beautiful Victoria Bentley his Queen!
description.37: Iron Man - at the mercy of the Maggia! How can Iron Man defeat the seemingly unstoppable Whiplash?
description.38: A rare battle between the Hulk and the Sub-Mariner! Who will emerge on top? Or just be submerged?
description.39: With Thor's full power not yet restored, the Thunder God proves prime bait for the Wrecker!
description.41: The ever-lovin' Thing is back! No longer possessed by the Mad Thinker, Ben Grimm joins his teammates in battling the Thinker's android! Plus, is this the end of the road for Mr. Fantastic and the Invisible Girl?
description.42: A still amnesiac Spider-Man must contend with the police, military, and worst of all: Ka-Zar and Zabu!
description.43: Hercules discovers the real reason behind Olympus' desertion, but can the Lion of Olympus defeat this new evil?  Meanwhile, Magneto persuades Quicksilver to rejoin his cause for Mutant domination, but has Quicksilver gone too far this time?
description.47: Using the nullifier device he stole Doc Ock convinces Spider-Man that he is one of the Doctor's henchmen!
description.48: After finding Olympus completely deserted, Hercules starts searching for clues. Dane Whitman vows to use his uncle's invention for good, and becomes the new Black Knight. Meanwhile, Quicksilver and the Scarlet Witch are held captive by Magneto.
description.49: The Fantastic Four have been pegged for murder, and Daredevil must save the team! The Trapster runs amok through New York City, but when the Man Without Fear is hot on your trails, even the biggest baddie doesn't stand a chance! Will this be Trapster's last stand? Plus, Debbie Harris returns to Foggy's life.
description.51: Dr. Strange finds himself transported to a strange world where he has to fight gigantic and monstrous creatures in his search for Victoria Bentley!
description.52: The Maggia have returned to destroy Iron Man, but they've got a new weapon up their sleeve - the mysterious figure known only as Whiplash! Plus: Captain America receives a distress call from Wakanda, where he must go to aid the Black Panther!
description.53: This story puts the question to the test: "Just HOW MUCH can the Hulk withstand"?
description.54: All Asgardians on Earth have been removed of their powers! Who is behind this sorcery? Plus, the Wrecker's first appearance!
description.56: The FF quashed the Mad Thinker...but now they must contend with a brainwashed Thing! Will Reed, Sue and Johnny be able to go full force against one of their own? All this and the Thinker's android!
description.59: Otto Octavius put Aunt May in the hospital. Now Spider-Man's got one thing on his mind: revenge!
description.60: The First Appearance of Dane Whitman, the Black Knight!  Plus, the Avengers are rocked to their core as Captain America leaves the team. Meanwhile, Magneto returns to earth from outer space to lure the Scarlet Witch and Quicksilver back into his clutches. And Hercules makes a shocking discovery.
description.62: The Trapster wants the legal advice of Nelson & Murdock- but he doesn't want to pay for it! Foggy and Matt receive a very unwelcome visitor, when a distraught Trapster crashes their office. Daredevil must investigate a murder plot...involving himself!
description.64: The beautiful mystic, Victoria Bentley, is in grave danger! Dr. Strange and Nebulos must face the dreadful Living Tribunal!
description.65: Iron Man is able to overcome the Grey Gargoyle...but at a terrible cost!
description.66: Hulk is tricked into attacking an Air Force base!
description.67: Loki posts Thor's bail, but that's where his good will ends. Thor vs. Loki! And the Thunder God has never been this vulnerable!
description.69: The Thing goes berserk! After the Mad Thinker's experiment, Ben Grimm goes on a violent spree against his teammates! Will Grimm finally get his chance to eliminate Reed Richards?
description.70: Captain Marvel (Mar-Vell) in his very first appearance!
description.72: Get ready for an epic battle between Spider-Man and the Human Torch! Plus, two mysterious guest villains make their appearance!
description.73: Spider-Man faces off against Doctor Octopus on the lawn of the Parker house! With Aunt May caught in the crossfire, ol' Webhead will have to think fast if he wants to save her!
description.74: Black Widow makes a full recovery, but is she going to remain an Avenger? The Wasp and Goliath battle the vengeful Whirlwind to a standstill. Plus, giant ants and more in this explosive issue!
description.76: The Beetle tells Daredevil about the man beneath the armored villain. Who was Abner Jenkins before he was Daredevil's foe? DD's secret identity is threatened when Beetle plans to reveal Murdock's face at the '67 World Fair! Will Daredevil be able to escape before he becomes six o' clock news?
description.77: Black Panther and the Inhumans storm the Psycho-Man's base, where they must do battle with...Lockjaw!? But that's not all, as Reed and Sue have a stunning announcement that will change the Fantastic Four forever!
description.79: The Gaff presents Fury with his new car-- a Ferrari 330/P4 Berlinetta, which is made entirely out of clear fiberglass, making it "completely invisible" from 100 feet away!
description.80: The Grey Gargoyle has succeeded where so many have failed - he has DEFEATED IRON MAN! Who can possibly save Tony Stark now? And to make matters worse, Steve Rogers is considering the unthinkable...retiring as Captain America!?
description.81: The Hulk meets with a group that seeks to end war on Earth. But why is this organization turning to the irradiated man-monster?
description.82: Sif and Balder watch helplessly as a de-powered Thor faces a debacle with the Circus of Crime. Will Odin find the mercy to make his son worthy again?
description.84: A cure for Ben Grimm? Mister Fantastic collaborates with a renowned doctor to reverse the Thing's mutations. But will the procedure go off without a hitch? Johnny introduces his crew to Crystal!
description.85: Foggy, Karen, and "Mike Murdock" hit the road and head to Montreal. But why? The Beetle may have escaped from Daredevil's clutches, but can he escape the iron fists of DD's alter ego? A train battle ensues between DD and the Beetle!
description.87: After Dr. Strange helps the evil Baron Mordo gain additional powers, Mordo turns on Strange and they must battle before Mordo scourges our mystic hero from the Earth!
description.88: The First Appearance of M.O.D.O.K.!   George Tarleton is radically transformed into M.O.D.O.K. after an experiment with A.I.M. and the Cosmic Cube goes awry!  When Sharon Carter goes undercover at A.I.M. and is discovered, Captain America will come face-to-very-large-face with M.O.D.O.K.!
description.89: The Evolutionary, by use of extreme aging powers, turns himself into a god-like figure.
description.90: The Ringmaster has hypnotized Thor into becoming his next, big act...but will the Thunder God go down without a fight? Odin has stripped Thor of his divine powers- and the timing couldn't be worse!
description.92: Deep in Lock 41 of the Beehive, Alicia encounters some of the organization's horrifying experiments. 'Him' emerges from a cocoon, intent on the destruction of its creators. The FF pulls off their most daring rescue mission yet!
description.93: While Peter and Gwen attend a science symposium, Doc Ock attacks! The 8-limbed menace aims to make off with a piece of military hardware, but Spidey's got something to say about that!
description.94: A grand celebration is held in honor of the Avengers, as Hercules is offered a spot on the team. But deep in the shadows Super-Adaptoid lurks, waiting for the perfect moment to pounce.
description.99: The Kingpin has an unconscious Spidey and J. Jonah Jameson sealed up tight in a watery deathtrap! If they want to get out while still breathing, Jameson will have to wake Spider-Man up from his afternoon nap...

1.text: The X-Men have been defeated by Magneto. But what has stayed his hand in delivering the killing stroke?!

9.text: When Loki transports the Hulk to Asgard, the Warriors Three rush to meet the Jade Giant!

15.text: During a heist on the open seas, Magneto is confronted by the X-Men!

20.text: This fantastic comic is all about origins! And who doesn't love an overload of origin stories?! Including "The Origin of... Stuporman!" I wonder who that could be!

31.text: In their battle with the Sub-Human Grotesk, one of the X-Men will pay the ultimate price!

40.text: A strange creature altered by atomic radiation emerges in the surface world and fights the X-Men.

45.text: In "The Wedding of Spidey-Man, or...With This Ring, I Thee Web!", we wonder, who is the lucky bride?? Similarly, in "The Human Scorch Has To... Meet the Family!", Scorch has a meeting with the in-laws! This should go over well!

55.text: The X-Men encounter an unusual alien android in the arctic.

58.text: Three spoofy stories sure to make you bust in laughter! Here, the first appearance of the ever-hapless Forbush Man! He once was a lowly office worker at Marvel Comics…but through the power of perseverance, he now is a self-made (and not fully realized) super hero!

68.text: The final confrontation between Factor Three and the X-Men!

75.text: Featuring: "Defeated by the Evil Electrico"! And meet Splat Murdock…A.K.A. Scaredevil! No, not MATT Murdock. Who the heck is that??

83.text: The X-Men race against the clock as Factor Three's plan is put into motion.

91.text: Factor Three's membership revealed! The X-Men on trial! Factor Three plans on inciting a global conflict and only the Uncanny X-Men can stop them.

96.text: Four more spoofy stories that will tickle your funny bone! Witness the transformation of Dr. Darn Bloke…into the Mighty Sore of Jazzgard! Then, it’s the origin of Brucie Banter and his grouchy, teenage-hating alter ego…the Inedible Bulk! And stay tuned for “The Honest-to-Irving, True-Blue, Top-Secret Original Origin Of Charlie America”! There’s not much super about this soldier!

98.text:
Daredevil's having a tough week. A flu bug has rendered his radar power useless, a Yakuza gang is trying to reclaim their power in Hell's Kitchen, and there's a murder to be solved. Now, he has to deal with a visitor from his time in prison-Carlos LaMuerto, a.k.a. the Black Tarantula. Carlos has been released, and he's looking to Matt Murdock for some help in setting up a new life on the outside. Will Murdock and LaMuerto end up as allies, or foes? Will Black Tarantula really go straight, or will his inner demons lure him back to his crime-lord past?
48 PGS./Rated T  ...$3.99
